variable nrrtemp
;
;
INUMBER 1682
NAME 384
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 5
MISC
IFPREVERB read -1
  ECHO PLAYER You open the book to find that it is a journal of some sort.
  ECHO PLAYER As you turn the pages it becomes clear that a elementalist took refuge on this
  ECHO PLAYER island to study a great artifact. Apparently something went wrong and he was
  ECHO PLAYER severly injured.
  ECHO PLAYER The last page is almost illegible, but you can make out that he hid the object
  ECHO PLAYER in an underwater cave near the beach and that he warded it with ice.
  ECHO ALL The book suddenly looses form, changing to water and seeping into the floor.
  REMOVEITEM -1
ENDIF
;
; Greater Elemental
MNUMBER 132
ADJECTIVE 9
NAME elemental
;Description dude!!!
;  Make sure you include the fact they have 
;  claws to cut through rock with!!!
*DESCRIPTION_START
The creature before you resembles a normal water elemental only in shape, it 
looms above you and has claws of ice that look as if they could break rock.
*DESCRIPTION_END
HUMAN
RACE 21
ETERNAL
DISCORPORATE
ATTACK1 500
BODY 750
EXTRABODY 500
DEFENSE 175
ARMOR 50
SPEED 2
STRATEGY 501
WEAPON 1703 -1 10
MAGICWEAPON 21
SPELL 121
SPELLSKILL 300
SPELLUSE 20
MANA 500
; entangle
IMMUNITY 0 0
; crushing
IMMUNITY 1 1
; edged weapons
IMMUNITY 2 1
; heat 0x dmg
IMMUNITY 3 1
; electricity
IMMUNITY 4 1
; cold 2x dmg
IMMUNITY 5 3
; charm,sleep
IMMUNITY 6 0
; life affecting
IMMUNITY 7 0
; death crits
IMMUNITY 9 0
;
; Text stuff goes here!
;
TEXI The blow passes through the body of the elemental without any effect.
TEXD disapears in a splash of water.
TEXM A greater elemental splashes
TEXE A greater elemental rises from the pool.
TEXS A greater elemental seems to shimmer slightly.
TEXL A greater elemental flashes for a moment.
TEXQ The elemental stops shimmering.
;
;
NUMBER 2300
NAME Sandy Beach
PLAIN
DAY_LIGHT	
CHANNEL 134
REGION 131
MONSTER_GROUP 13
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are standing on a beach. To the south of you stretches water as far as you
can see, while the beach runs to the northeast and northwest from here. To the
north is impenetrable jungle.
An opening hangs in the air.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 2308
EXIT NW 2301
EXIT ABOVE 2310
; item 0 water
ITEM 0 1062
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The water splashes up onto the beach in gentle waves.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You splash around in the water for a few moments before moving back onto the beach.
  ECHO OTHERS You see %N splash about in the water for a few moments and then move back onto the beach.
ENDIF
IFTOUCH 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The water feels cool as it splashes against you.
  ECHO OTHERS You see %N touch the water.
;ITEM 2 OPENING
ITEM 2 72 VAL2=343
IFVERB dig -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You dig in the sand.
  ECHO OTHERS You see %N dig in the sand.
  RANDOM nrrtemp 1 100 0
  IFVAR nrrtemp > 70
    ECHO PLAYER After a few moments, you find shell in the sand.
    NEWITEM -1 1138 ADJ1=281 VAL1=1
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
;
