NUMBER 2309
NAME Underwater Cave
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
CHANNEL 134
REGION 131
*DESCRIPTION_START
This cave seems to have been formed by the swirling action of the water at
some point. The floor is smooth rock and the air is stale, but breathable.
Mounds of ice cover the floor and an opening leads back into the water.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;item 0 icy mound
ITEM 0 916 ADJ1=166
IFPREVERB CAST 0
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR SPELLNUM = 100
  ECHO PLAYER You cast you spell at an icy mound causing it to melt.
  ECHO OTHERS You see %N cast at a mound of ice.
  EQUAL SPELLNUM 999
  ENDIF
  IFVAR SPELLNUM = 117
  ECHO PLAYER You cast you spell at an icy mound causing it to melt.
  ECHO OTHERS You see %N cast at a mound of ice.
  EQUAL SPELLNUM 999
  ENDIF
  IFVAR SPELLNUM = 118
  ECHO PLAYER You cast you spell at an icy mound causing it to melt.
  ECHO OTHERS You see %N cast at a mound of ice.
  EQUAL SPELLNUM 999
  ENDIF
  IFVAR SPELLNUM = 999
    EQUAL SPELLNUM 0
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER Nothing Happens.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB STOMP -1
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
    CLEARVERB
    NEWITEM -1 64 adj1=29 adj2=77
    ECHO ALL A mound melts to reveal a blue crystal sphere.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
